1️⃣ Account kya hai?
Account = External system user account
Ye represent karta hai konsa user kis application me hai aur uske entitlements / groups.

()Account Class Full Methods List:-
1️⃣ Basic                                       Identity Methods
Method	                                         Description
setName(String name)----------------------Account ka username set kare
getName()---------------------------------Account ka username return kare
setApplicationName(String appName)--------Account ka application name set kare
getApplicationName()----------------------Account ka application name return kare
setIdentity(Identity identity)------------Account ke linked SailPoint Identity set kare
getIdentity()-----------------------------Linked identity return kare

2️⃣ Attributes / Custom Data:-
Method	                                          Description
setAttribute(String key, Object value)--------Custom attribute set kare
getAttribute(String key)----------------------Attribute value return kare
getAttributes()-------------------------------Saare attributes map me return kare
setAttributes(Map<String, Object> attrs)------Multiple attributes ek saath set kare

3️⃣ Status / Management:-
Method	                                Description
setManaged(Boolean flag)--------------Account managed hai ya nahi set kare
isManaged()---------------------------True/False return kare
setStatus(String status)--------------Account status set kare (Active/Disabled/Locked)
getStatus()---------------------------Account status return kare

4️⃣ Entitlements / Roles / Groups:-
Method	                                               Description
setEntitlements(List<String> entitlements)-------Account ke roles/groups set kare
getEntitlements()--------------------------------Roles/groups return kare
addEntitlement(String entitlement)---------------Single role add kare
removeEntitlement(String entitlement)------------Single role remove kare

5️⃣ Account Lifecycle / Provisioning:-
Method	                                                   Description
setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation op)------------Provisioning operation set kare (Add/Remove/Modify)
getOperation()-----------------------------------------Provisioning operation return kare
setSource(String source)-------------------------------Account source (e.g., workflow, connector) set kare
getSource()--------------------------------------------Account source return kare

6️⃣ Metadata / Extra Info:-
Method	                                  Description
setCreated(Date date)------------Account creation date set kare
getCreated()---------------------Account creation date return kare
setModified(Date date)-----------Last modified date set kare
getModified()--------------------Last modified date return kare
setNativeIdentity(String nativeId)----------Application ka native user ID set kare
getNativeIdentity()-------------------------Native user ID return kare

1️⃣ setParent(String parent):-
Ye method Account object ka parent set karne ke liye use hota hai.
Matlab Account ke upar ka object ya hierarchy specify karna.
Ye generally complex applications ya nested accounts me use hota hai.

Example:-
Account account = new Account();
account.setName("rahul123");

// Parent object set karna
account.setParent("FinanceDepartment");

System.out.println("Parent set to: " + account.getParent());

Output:-
Parent set to: FinanceDepartment
Matlab ye account FinanceDepartment ke under hai.
-----------------
1️⃣ setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation op):-
Ye method account ke upar ka provisioning operation set karta hai.
Possible operations:-
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Add → New access/account create karna
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Modify → Existing account ya access update karna
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Remove → Access ya account remove karna.

1️⃣ setOperation(ProvisioningPlan.Operation op):-
Ye method account ke upar ka provisioning operation set karta hai.
Possible operations:-
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Add → New access/account create karna
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Modify → Existing account ya access update karna
ProvisioningPlan.Operation.Remove → Access ya account remove karna.

3️⃣ setSource(String source):-
Ye method account ka source set karta hai, jaha se ye account aa raha hai:-
Example: "Workflow", "Connector", "Manual", "API"
Ye audit aur logging ke liye important hai.
Example:-
account.setSource("Workflow");
System.out.println("Account source: " + account.getSource());

Output:-
Account source: Workflow

